  "texts": [
    "A semantic image segmentation that serves as the foundation for radiotherapy planning, for example, would require exact contours (FP2.1 -particular importance of structure boundaries = TRUE).",
    "On the other hand, for a cell segmentation problem that serves as prerequisite for cell tracking, the object centers may be much more important (FP2.3 -particular importance of structure center(line) = TRUE).",
    "Both problems could be tackled with identical network architectures, but the validation metrics should be different.",
    "FP3 -Target structure-related properties represent inherent properties of target structure(s) (if any), such as the size, size variability and the shape.",
    "Here, the term target structures can refer to any object/structure of interest, such as cells, vessels, medical instruments or tumors."
